 and back to Frontend.\n  - Checkout Service propagating delays possibly due to Payment, Shipping, and Cart interactions.\n  - Deadlock or data lock scenarios in cart operations or Redis operations.\n\n- **Network Observations:**\n  - Clear network-induced latency in the trace data where cart service duration greatly exceeds normal, possibly due to network congestion or task serialization on server side.\n  \nThese trace anomalies point to central issues within the Cart and Checkout services, with propagated delays or backlogs potentially affecting broader system interactions. More targeted probe or direct inspection on Redis and Cart module should be conducted to confirm specific issues at backend storage or service logic level.\n\nPlease proceed with further diagnostics focusing on the Cart and Redis services to isolate the root cause effectively."}
